I like the concept of this game. It is an endless runner, but it is fast paced and exciting unlike most. The graphics are pleasing and controller support is nice. I have a few problems with it. It gets so fast paced that it is difficult for me to see what is ahead, so I have to collide the character with objects to slow down which I find strange. There is a slight delay between the character hitting the ground and being able to jump, which makes all the difference if the character lands on the edge of a building. The music is nice at first but gets repetitive after a while, hardly what would warrant headphones. It would be nice if a few songs shuffled. I may just suck at this game, but it is nearly impossible to judge how to jump from a suspended billboard or I-beam without being able to see the buildings underneath and the platforms that fall from the sky which I am expected to jump on are nearly impossible to judge before I am forced to jump and send the character into the abyss.
